definition: to join head to tail/bumper-to-bumper (of traffic jam)
head/chief/first (occasion, thing etc)/classifier for poems, songs etc
tail/remainder/remnant/extremity/sixth of the 28 constellations/classifier for fish
horse's tail/pointed posterior section of a locust etc
each other/one another/mutually/fret on the neck of a pipa 琵琶[pi2 pa5] (a fret on the soundboard is called a 品[pin3])
appearance/portrait/picture/government minister/(physics) phase/(literary) to appraise (esp. by scrutinizing physical features)/to read sb's fortune (by physiognomy, palmistry etc)
to receive/to answer (the phone)/to meet or welcome sb/to connect/to catch/to join/to extend/to take one's turn on duty/to take over for sb

sentences.english: It was bumper-to-bumper all the way from school.
sentences.chinese: 从学校过来的路上都是一辆辆首尾相接的车。

sentences.english: A car turned over and blocked the road, so all the traffic was held up.
sentences.chinese: 从学校过来的路上都是一辆辆首尾相接的车。

sentences.english: The cars backed up for miles.
sentences.chinese: 汽车拥塞，首尾相接长达数英里。

sentences.english: The circle queue is a type of dynamic data structure.
sentences.chinese: 首尾相接的循环队列是一种动态的数据结构。

sentences.english: Suppose time is a circle, bending back on itself.
sentences.chinese: 设想时间是一个圆圈，弯转过来首尾相接。

sentences.english: Or, if they were collected and put end to end, how many round trips to the moon and back could they make?
sentences.chinese: 如果把它们首尾相接，可以往返地球与月球间多少次？
